1
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:49,333
[birds chirping]

2
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:52,083
Okay, let's take the roll,
shall we?

3
00:01:52,166 --> 00:01:53,958
Kenya Misaki?

4
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:57,666
Ryota Sekiguchi?

5
00:01:58,750 --> 00:02:00,083
Gale Gibson?

6
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:03,333
Alice Rondo?

7
00:02:04,791 --> 00:02:06,416
Chloe Aubert?

8
00:02:07,708 --> 00:02:09,250
Hey, come on, kids.

9
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:11,625
When I call your name
you need to say "here," got it?

10
00:02:11,708 --> 00:02:13,541
Just call it out nice and loud.

11
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:18,583
All right, I think I've got
a pretty good grasp

12
00:02:18,666 --> 00:02:20,041
on the situation.

13
00:02:20,125 --> 00:02:23,166
So, it's about time
I call in a friend of mine.

14
00:02:25,458 --> 00:02:26,416
[RANGA growling]

15
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,166
-[RIMURU] Kenya Misaki?
-Here!

16
00:02:28,250 --> 00:02:31,333
-[RIMURU] Ryota Sekiguchi?
-Here.

17
00:02:31,416 --> 00:02:33,333
-[RIMURU] Gale Gibson?
-Here!

18
00:02:33,416 --> 00:02:35,875
-[RIMURU] Alice Rondo?
-Uh, here!

19
00:02:35,958 --> 00:02:39,083
-[RIMURU] Chloe Aubert?
-Here.

20
00:02:39,166 --> 00:02:41,250
Good job! Now we're talkin'!

21
00:02:43,583 --> 00:02:47,875
Hey! Calling in that monster dog
to threaten us is dirty!

22
00:02:47,958 --> 00:02:49,750
[groaning]

23
00:02:49,833 --> 00:02:51,541
[RANGA]
My name is Ranga.

24
00:02:51,625 --> 00:02:53,333
Don't forget that, child.

25
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:55,000
Okay, okay, I get it.

26
00:02:55,083 --> 00:02:56,625
[RIMURU]
Mm-hmm.

27
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:58,541
Look, you're already
good friends.

28
00:02:58,625 --> 00:02:59,500
How wonderful.

29
00:02:59,583 --> 00:03:01,125
My name is Rimuru,

30
00:03:01,208 --> 00:03:03,791
and starting today I'm your new,
insanely awesome teacher.

31
00:03:03,875 --> 00:03:07,208
Also, I'm probably
not as patient as Shizu.

32
00:03:07,291 --> 00:03:08,375
So keep that in mind.

33
00:03:10,333 --> 00:03:12,625
Oh, my, so quiet!

34
00:03:12,708 --> 00:03:14,333
[growling]

35
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:15,708
[ALL]
Yes, sir!

36
00:03:15,791 --> 00:03:17,208
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

37
00:03:18,416 --> 00:03:21,083
Looks like gaining their trust
is gonna be tough.

38
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:24,666
Not that I can blame them.

39
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:26,208
They were summoned to this world

40
00:03:26,291 --> 00:03:28,458
and then tossed aside
like garbage.

41
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:32,875
Right. Pop quiz time.
Doesn't that sound like a blast?

42
00:03:32,958 --> 00:03:36,000
No. Since when
did tests become fun?

43
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:37,000
I hate them.

44
00:03:37,083 --> 00:03:38,291
[choking]

45
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:40,250
You can't give us a quiz
on the first day.

46
00:03:40,333 --> 00:03:42,125
Yeah, it's against the rules.

47
00:03:42,208 --> 00:03:45,416
Calm down
before you hurt yourselves.

48
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:46,958
Look, this is important,

49
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:49,166
and honestly something
you kids need right now.

50
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:51,625
Everyone knows
we're gonna kick the bucket.

51
00:03:51,708 --> 00:03:53,208
So why should
we have to study?

52
00:03:53,291 --> 00:03:54,458
It's just a huge waste of time.

53
00:03:54,541 --> 00:03:56,625
Yeah. He's got a point.

54
00:03:56,708 --> 00:03:59,791
And the other teachers always
let us do whatever we want to.

55
00:03:59,875 --> 00:04:02,291
Exactly, we haven't had to study
since we got here.

56
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:04,791
I just wanna read
my books in peace.

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,958
You're the worst!
Bossy jerk-face!

58
00:04:08,041 --> 00:04:09,375
[RIMURU]
Mm-hmm.

59
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,541
You guys have a lot
of fair points.

60
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,000
But relax.

61
00:04:13,083 --> 00:04:14,958
I called it a pop quiz
but it's more like a game.

62
00:04:15,041 --> 00:04:16,541
A game?

63
00:04:16,625 --> 00:04:18,250
You got it.

64
00:04:18,333 --> 00:04:22,000
And it's designed to let you
get your frustrations out.

65
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:23,500
[KIDS murmur]

66
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,041
[RIMURU] Basically, we're gonna
have one-on-one mock battles.

67
00:04:28,125 --> 00:04:29,750
You've got ten minutes.

68
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,291
If you can take me
out in that time,

69
00:04:31,375 --> 00:04:32,916
I'll declare you the winner.

70
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,791
All you guys have to do
is beat me.

71
00:04:34,875 --> 00:04:37,291
-Is that it?
-[RIMURU] Yup.

72
00:04:37,375 --> 00:04:39,541
-Ten minutes?
-[RIMURU] Uh-huh.

73
00:04:39,625 --> 00:04:42,458
Ha! As long as you don't use
that drool machine,

74
00:04:42,541 --> 00:04:43,958
we won't need ten minutes.

75
00:04:44,041 --> 00:04:46,541
Yeah, using him
would be overkill.

76
00:04:46,625 --> 00:04:48,833
-Ranga, don't interfere, 'kay?
-[RANGA] Right.

77
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:51,458
Oh, yeah, this will be easy.

78
00:04:51,541 --> 00:04:53,458
All I wanna do is read my book.

79
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:56,708
Right. Hey, Ryota,
can you be the ref?

80
00:04:56,791 --> 00:04:59,125
[RYOTA]
Uh... Mm-hmm.

81
00:04:59,208 --> 00:05:01,708
Thanks. All right,
who wants to go first?

82
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,166
I'll take you on.

83
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:06,708
Ahh. They say fortune favors
the bold, eh, Kenya?

84
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:10,208
[KENYA]
Can we use these weapons?

85
00:05:10,291 --> 00:05:11,833
[RIMURU]
Sure, knock yourself out.

86
00:05:11,916 --> 00:05:14,916
But if you end up losing,
you gotta show me some respect.

87
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:18,208
Ha! I've never lost a fight
to anyone but Miss Shizu,

88
00:05:18,291 --> 00:05:19,416
so you'd better be ready.

89
00:05:19,500 --> 00:05:21,458
Why don't you
save the smack talk

90
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:22,666
for when you've beaten me?

91
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,041
[KENYA grunts]

92
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:25,458
[RIMURU] I'm hoping this fight
will burn off

93
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:27,583
some of that excess
magicule energy.

94
00:05:27,666 --> 00:05:31,000
If we get rid of it now
maybe it'll save their lives.

95
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:32,750
Uh... Please begin.

96
00:05:33,791 --> 00:05:35,000
[yells]

97
00:05:36,375 --> 00:05:37,291
Huh?

98
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:38,708
[grunting]
You!

99
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:43,000
-You've got this, Ken!
-Don't lose!

100
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:45,583
I will get you!

101
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:48,750
[RIMURU] You move pretty fast,
but not fast enough.

102
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,958
[grunts]

103
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,500
[grunts]

104
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:58,458
[yells]

105
00:05:58,541 --> 00:06:00,833
[RIMURU] Man, are those flames
made out of lame sauce?

106
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:02,291
The kid's got a lot of energy,

107
00:06:02,375 --> 00:06:05,041
but the weak fire show
is a massive waste of it.

108
00:06:05,125 --> 00:06:07,875
Listen,
instead of throwing fire,

109
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:09,750
try striking me
with some of that raw energy.

110
00:06:09,833 --> 00:06:11,166
Shut up!

111
00:06:11,250 --> 00:06:13,166
These are the same moves
that Miss Shizu used!

112
00:06:13,250 --> 00:06:14,458
Eat fire!

113
00:06:16,333 --> 00:06:18,750
♪

114
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:20,416
Stop. The time is up.

115
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:22,666
[panting]

116
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,458
Well, that's it.

117
00:06:24,541 --> 00:06:26,791
So you'd better get used
to calling me "Teach" now.

118
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:28,708
Man!

119
00:06:28,791 --> 00:06:29,875
[RIMURU]
Who's next?

120
00:06:29,958 --> 00:06:32,750
[KENYA crying]
You'll regret this!

121
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:36,166
Guess it's Chloe.

122
00:06:38,125 --> 00:06:40,541
Chloe,
don't push yourself, okay?

123
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:42,000
Yeah, please be careful.

124
00:06:44,208 --> 00:06:45,333
[RIMURU]
I don't know why,

125
00:06:45,416 --> 00:06:47,708
but this girl
seems familiar somehow.

126
00:06:47,791 --> 00:06:49,583
Like I've seen her before.

127
00:06:49,666 --> 00:06:50,750
-[RYOTA] Begin.
-[RIMURU gasps]

128
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,916
[RIMURU] Is she gonna
chuck a book at me?

129
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,916
That's crazy.

130
00:06:57,375 --> 00:07:01,000
Flow of water,
please ensnare my enemy.

131
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:02,041
Go, Water Jail.

132
00:07:02,125 --> 00:07:03,750
♪

133
00:07:06,208 --> 00:07:07,458
[RIMURU]
Oh!

134
00:07:07,541 --> 00:07:09,166
She's also a magic user?

135
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:17,500
This is legit.
I wonder if she's a prodigy.

136
00:07:17,583 --> 00:07:19,625
[CHLOE] So you know,
I can also make blades

137
00:07:19,708 --> 00:07:21,250
come out of the water
that's around you.

138
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:25,708
Admit defeat and I'll be happy
to withdraw them.

139
00:07:25,791 --> 00:07:27,541
But if you refuse me,
you'll die.

140
00:07:27,625 --> 00:07:30,750
[RIMURU] She's so young
and yet so frightening!

141
00:07:30,833 --> 00:07:32,541
Better hurry up, dude!

142
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:33,708
Admit defeat, already.

143
00:07:33,791 --> 00:07:34,875
Way to go, Chloe!

144
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:36,833
-Yeah, awesome job.
-Heck, yeah!

145
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,833
[RIMURU]
Your magic is top-notch.

146
00:07:41,666 --> 00:07:44,083
It's a real shame
that it's not gonna work on me.

147
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:46,125
♪

148
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:51,125
-Huh?
-[ALL gasp]

149
00:07:51,208 --> 00:07:53,666
[RIMURU] My Extra Skill
Magic Manipulation

150
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:55,666
makes escaping
that "Jail" a cinch.

151
00:07:55,750 --> 00:07:59,000
You're pretty good
with that water magic.

152
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:00,666
You should definitely
keep studying it.

153
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,500
[CHLOE whimpers]

154
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:08,791
[RIMURU]
She's crying. Sorry, kiddo.

155
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:10,583
But it's important
that you guys know

156
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:12,500
how big the power gap is
between us.

157
00:08:12,583 --> 00:08:14,416
[crying]

158
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:22,166
Don't hold it against me
if I kill you, okay?

159
00:08:25,708 --> 00:08:28,041
[RIMURU] Magic bullets,
and they look strong!

160
00:08:28,125 --> 00:08:29,125
Nope.

161
00:08:32,583 --> 00:08:33,750
That was yummy.

162
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:36,500
Hey, what gives, man?
You cheated!

163
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:39,083
Sorry. That's how things are.

164
00:08:39,166 --> 00:08:40,958
As long as you win the fight,
anything goes.

165
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:42,541
[whimpering]

166
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,208
[RIMURU]
Looks like Ryota's next.

167
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,666
He's seems a little more timid.

168
00:08:48,750 --> 00:08:50,708
Pretty much the exact opposite
of Kenya.

169
00:08:50,791 --> 00:08:52,083
Go, Ryota!

170
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:53,500
Beat him to a pulp, okay?!

171
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:56,708
[evil laughter]

172
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:58,708
[growls]

173
00:08:58,791 --> 00:09:01,291
[yelling]

174
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,541
[RIMURU]
Body Enhancement?

175
00:09:03,625 --> 00:09:06,500
Or is that the Berserker skill?

176
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:08,291
♪

177
00:09:10,916 --> 00:09:12,458
[yelling]

178
00:09:13,916 --> 00:09:15,708
[grunts]

179
00:09:15,791 --> 00:09:18,000
[snarling]

180
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:20,458
[RIMURU]
Nice strength enhancement.

181
00:09:20,541 --> 00:09:22,083
If he were fighting anyone else,

182
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:24,291
he'd probably put up
a decent fight.

183
00:09:24,375 --> 00:09:26,750
But I gotta dock points
for the rabid dog impression

184
00:09:26,833 --> 00:09:29,291
and total lack of control
in battle.

185
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,791
[yelling]

186
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:33,666
[stones crumbling]

187
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,833
Looks like it's my turn,
so prepare to suffer.

188
00:09:41,916 --> 00:09:43,375
Hmm!

189
00:09:43,458 --> 00:09:45,833
Watch and learn, losers, as I,
the amazing Lady Alice,

190
00:09:45,916 --> 00:09:48,125
enlighten you
on how to win a battle.

191
00:09:49,500 --> 00:09:51,791
Go! Okay, guys, attack.

192
00:09:51,875 --> 00:09:53,791
Take that jerk out!

193
00:09:53,875 --> 00:09:55,000
[RIMURU]
Huh?

194
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:59,500
Puppetry?
She's a Golem Master?

195
00:09:59,583 --> 00:10:01,833
♪

196
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:06,583
If she can fight this well
using stuffed animals,

197
00:10:06,666 --> 00:10:08,125
imagine what she could do
with dolls

198
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:10,875
made from special alloys
as her weapons instead.

199
00:10:10,958 --> 00:10:12,666
Out of the five kids,

200
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:16,083
her ability might be
the most promising.

201
00:10:16,166 --> 00:10:17,833
But it's kinda annoying.

202
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:19,791
Maybe I should incinerate
the things.

203
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,208
[GREAT SAGE]
Notice.

204
00:10:21,291 --> 00:10:23,583
The probability that this girl,
Alice Rondo,

205
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:25,333
would cry is 100 percent.

206
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:26,875
[RIMURU]
Yeah, maybe not.

207
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,250
Stop. The time is up.

208
00:10:31,083 --> 00:10:32,750
[RANGA panting]

209
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,208
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

210
00:10:36,291 --> 00:10:37,625
Doesn't look like
the magicule count

211
00:10:37,708 --> 00:10:40,000
in their bodies
has been reduced at all.

212
00:10:40,083 --> 00:10:41,500
I wonder,

213
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:43,625
can I separate them from
the energy using Degenerate?

214
00:10:43,708 --> 00:10:44,791
[GREAT SAGE]
Answer.

215
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:46,583
The energy has fused
with their souls

216
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,666
and therefore cannot
be separated from them.

217
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,625
[RIMURU]
That sucks.

218
00:10:50,708 --> 00:10:52,458
I don't know how much time
they have left,

219
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:54,625
so I'll have to look
for another way.

220
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,375
All right, listen up, gang.

221
00:10:58,458 --> 00:11:00,041
[ALL]
Hmm?

222
00:11:00,125 --> 00:11:02,583
As the five of you
have just witnessed,

223
00:11:02,666 --> 00:11:03,666
I am swol.

224
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:05,041
[ALL]
Huh?

225
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:07,750
I'm gonna make you a promise.

226
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:09,333
I will save all of you.

227
00:11:09,416 --> 00:11:11,041
You "promise"?

228
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:14,500
Yeah. I swear it on this mask.

229
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:17,291
-[ALL gasp]
-Is that Miss Shizu's?

230
00:11:17,375 --> 00:11:18,291
It sure is.

231
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:21,083
When Shizu entrusted this to me,

232
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:23,833
I think she was also
entrusting me with all of you.

233
00:11:25,583 --> 00:11:26,791
Fine, you win.

234
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:28,666
I've decided to trust you now.

235
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:31,208
Yeah, I'm gonna trust you, too.

236
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:34,791
I actually trusted you
from the moment I first met you.

237
00:11:34,875 --> 00:11:36,083
Thanks, traitors.

238
00:11:36,166 --> 00:11:37,375
Ugh, whatever.

239
00:11:37,458 --> 00:11:38,625
Guess I'll trust you, too.

240
00:11:38,708 --> 00:11:40,125
It'll be fine.

241
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:42,000
And besides, I really do think

242
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:43,791
he's a person
we can put our faith in.

243
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:46,166
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

244
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,208
Sounds good.

245
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:49,791
[RIMURU]
Wait.

246
00:11:49,875 --> 00:11:52,041
Didn't Shizu say she was
around the same age

247
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:55,291
as these kids when she was
summoned to this world?

248
00:11:55,375 --> 00:11:56,916
She said that Demon Lord Leon

249
00:11:57,000 --> 00:11:59,375
made the spirit of Ifrit
possess her.

250
00:12:00,958 --> 00:12:02,375
Could that be it?

251
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:04,583
-[GALE] Uh, sir?
-[RIMURU gasps]

252
00:12:07,875 --> 00:12:10,875
Are we clear?
I'll save you no matter what.

253
00:12:10,958 --> 00:12:13,375
Shizu's last request was
that I watch over you guys.

254
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:14,583
I won't abandon you.

255
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:18,250
[ALL] You're the best!
Thanks, Teach!

256
00:12:18,333 --> 00:12:19,958
[RIMURU]
They called me "Teach."

257
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:22,541
I'm so happy!

258
00:12:22,625 --> 00:12:26,166
From now on you guys
are my students!

259
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:28,166
[ALL]
Huh?

260
00:12:29,500 --> 00:12:30,875
[RIMURU]
Uh...

261
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:32,375
[RANGA panting]

262
00:12:35,625 --> 00:12:37,166
♪

263
00:12:37,250 --> 00:12:38,458
[RIMURU]
Vesta recently taught me

264
00:12:38,541 --> 00:12:40,125
how to use a Warp Portal,

265
00:12:40,208 --> 00:12:43,125
so I used it to go visit Treyni
in the Great Forest of Jura.

266
00:12:43,208 --> 00:12:45,291
[energy humming]

267
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:50,750
I think that if I can make
superior spirits

268
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:53,666
inhabit the kids the same way
Ifrit did with Shizu,

269
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:55,416
we might be able
to control their energy

270
00:12:55,500 --> 00:12:56,750
and save their lives.

271
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,750
[wind rushing]

272
00:13:01,208 --> 00:13:02,458
Lord Rimuru.

273
00:13:02,541 --> 00:13:03,750
What brings you here?

274
00:13:03,833 --> 00:13:05,750
[RIMURU]
What up, Treyni?

275
00:13:05,833 --> 00:13:08,291
Do you know where I can find
some superior spirits?

276
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,583
Let me think.

277
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,041
You could always
try a place called

278
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,375
"The Dwelling of Spirits,"

279
00:13:13,458 --> 00:13:15,291
which is ruled over
by the Queen of Spirits.

280
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,583
[RIMURU]
Sweet!

281
00:13:16,666 --> 00:13:18,333
That sounds exactly like
the kind of place

282
00:13:18,416 --> 00:13:19,291
I'm lookin' for.

283
00:13:19,375 --> 00:13:21,208
Yes.

284
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:22,125
However...

285
00:13:22,208 --> 00:13:23,458
[RIMURU]
Huh?

286
00:13:23,541 --> 00:13:25,041
[TREYNI]
You see,

287
00:13:25,125 --> 00:13:27,541
there are several entrances
to that domain.

288
00:13:27,625 --> 00:13:29,458
But I'm afraid
that the only one I know of

289
00:13:29,541 --> 00:13:31,125
has long since vanished.

290
00:13:31,208 --> 00:13:32,750
[RIMURU]
What?

291
00:13:32,833 --> 00:13:35,833
The Queen of Spirits who we
once served has passed away.

292
00:13:35,916 --> 00:13:38,500
A rather long time ago,
actually.

293
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:41,083
And I have no connection
to the current Queen.

294
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:42,541
I don't know where she resides.

295
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:44,750
[RIMURU]
Got it.

296
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:47,500
[TREYNI] I'm sorry that
I couldn't be more help to you.

297
00:13:47,583 --> 00:13:48,791
[RIMURU]
It's okay.

298
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:57,750
♪

299
00:14:00,916 --> 00:14:04,166
[RIMURU] Don't worry.
I'm gonna keep my promise.

300
00:14:09,916 --> 00:14:12,125
♪

301
00:14:12,208 --> 00:14:14,666
[RIMURU] It's been a month
since I became a teacher.

302
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:16,541
I've spent that time
trying to figure out

303
00:14:16,625 --> 00:14:18,208
where the superior spirits live,

304
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:20,500
but I've yet to find
anything useful.

305
00:14:21,916 --> 00:14:23,666
Today, we're having a picnic,

306
00:14:23,750 --> 00:14:26,208
because everyone needs
a break sometimes.

307
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:28,458
Okay.

308
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:29,958
Before we have lunch,

309
00:14:30,041 --> 00:14:31,708
I think we should do
a little bit of combat training.

310
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:34,166
[ALL grunt]

311
00:14:34,250 --> 00:14:37,666
Whoever does their best
will get a reward.

312
00:14:37,750 --> 00:14:39,166
-No way!
-[ALICE screams]

313
00:14:39,250 --> 00:14:40,291
[CHLOE gasps]

314
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:41,875
A new manga!

315
00:14:41,958 --> 00:14:43,291
[yells]

316
00:14:43,375 --> 00:14:45,291
Oh, man, I can't wait to see
what happens next!

317
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:47,458
For sure. Things were just
starting to get really good

318
00:14:47,541 --> 00:14:49,083
in the last issue.

319
00:14:49,166 --> 00:14:51,541
Back off, I'm gonna read it
before any of you idiots do!

320
00:14:52,916 --> 00:14:53,875
I like manga.

321
00:14:53,958 --> 00:14:55,625
Yeah, it's pretty cool.

322
00:14:55,708 --> 00:14:57,625
Not that I know a lot about
Japanese cartoons

323
00:14:57,708 --> 00:15:00,250
and comic books,
but it's still interesting.

324
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,500
Now then, which of you
wants to go first?

325
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:03,875
Me! I do!

326
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:04,916
No, me! Me!

327
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:06,583
-Uh, I'll go.
-Pick me!

328
00:15:06,666 --> 00:15:07,791
[RYOTA]
Me, first.

329
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:09,333
[GALE]
No way. Let me go first, Teach.

330
00:15:09,416 --> 00:15:11,625
-[overlapping chatter]
-Come on, man, I'm begging ya!

331
00:15:11,708 --> 00:15:13,000
[KENYA exhales]

332
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:15,416
Aw, man, I can't believe
I lost again today.

333
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:18,000
Yeah, this isn't fair, Teach,
you're like way stronger.

334
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,458
And aren't you supposed to
take it easy on a lady,

335
00:15:20,541 --> 00:15:21,708
you stupid jerk?!

336
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:23,458
I need to practice
my magic some more.

337
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,875
No matter what
we can't beat the guy!

338
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,666
[laughing]

339
00:15:30,500 --> 00:15:31,958
Sorry, teenyboppers.

340
00:15:32,041 --> 00:15:34,250
But you're dreaming if you think
you'll ever defeat me.

341
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:37,250
[KIDS booing]

342
00:15:37,333 --> 00:15:39,166
[laughing]

343
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:40,541
You did try your best, at least,

344
00:15:40,625 --> 00:15:42,541
so I suppose
I'll let you have this manga.

345
00:15:42,625 --> 00:15:44,125
-[energy humming]
-[RIMURU gasps]

346
00:15:44,208 --> 00:15:45,583
Something wrong?

347
00:15:46,625 --> 00:15:47,750
-[RANGA growling]
-[wind gushing]

348
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:49,833
♪

349
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:53,250
That's odd.
The air pressure changed.

350
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:54,666
[GREAT SAGE]
Notice.

351
00:15:54,750 --> 00:15:56,958
High-density energy
has been detected.

352
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,833
This is due in part
to a Sky Dragon.

353
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:01,833
A Sky Dragon?

354
00:16:04,416 --> 00:16:06,791
[SKY DRAGON screeching]

355
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:08,625
-[KENYA groaning]
-[ALICE screaming]

356
00:16:08,708 --> 00:16:09,875
[RIMURU gasps]

357
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:15,708
Crazy. Is it like a stray?

358
00:16:15,791 --> 00:16:17,458
It's heading
towards the capital.

359
00:16:17,541 --> 00:16:19,333
True that.

360
00:16:19,416 --> 00:16:20,541
I should go do something.

361
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:22,041
[KENYA]
Huh?

362
00:16:22,125 --> 00:16:24,333
[RIMURU]
I can't just let it run free.

363
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:26,500
I mean, somebody could
get hurt, right?

364
00:16:26,583 --> 00:16:29,750
Ranga, you stay behind
and protect the kids, okay?

365
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:32,750
[RANGA] Master, are you sure
you don't want me to go

366
00:16:32,833 --> 00:16:34,625
and give it a good chomping?

367
00:16:34,708 --> 00:16:36,416
Nah, you'd better
leave that guy to me.

368
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,875
Besides, I gotta put on
a good show for these brats.

369
00:16:39,958 --> 00:16:41,291
[RANGA]
Of course.

370
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,583
[KENYA]
Uh, Teach?

371
00:16:42,666 --> 00:16:44,625
I know you're like
mad swol and all that,

372
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,791
but you can't possibly
beat a Sky Dragon.

373
00:16:46,875 --> 00:16:47,958
Yeah, for sure.

374
00:16:48,041 --> 00:16:49,416
If you bite
the bullet in battle,

375
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:51,458
then who's gonna save us
from dying at a young age?

376
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:53,250
Chill out, I'm not stupid enough

377
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,666
to take on something
I can't easily beat.

378
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,791
I'll be back in a jiffy.

379
00:16:57,875 --> 00:16:59,541
-Hold up, Teach!
-[ALL] Please, Teach!

380
00:17:00,916 --> 00:17:02,500
Hang on to this for me.

381
00:17:02,583 --> 00:17:04,458
[ALL gasp]

382
00:17:04,541 --> 00:17:05,583
[BOTH grunt]

383
00:17:05,666 --> 00:17:07,833
[overlapping chatter]

384
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,791
♪

385
00:17:13,208 --> 00:17:14,833
Wait, he can fly?

386
00:17:14,916 --> 00:17:16,208
Awesome.

387
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:21,625
I should probably
disguise myself a bit.

388
00:17:23,791 --> 00:17:24,875
There, that's better.

389
00:17:28,166 --> 00:17:29,416
[ALL screaming]

390
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:31,083
[SKY DRAGON screeching]

391
00:17:31,166 --> 00:17:32,416
[panting]

392
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,208
♪

393
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:41,541
[screeching]

394
00:17:41,625 --> 00:17:43,250
[CAPTAIN]
Aim!

395
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:44,708
Fire!

396
00:17:44,791 --> 00:17:46,291
[arrows clanging]

397
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:49,625
[energy charging]

398
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:54,875
[explosions]

399
00:17:54,958 --> 00:17:56,833
[BOTH groaning]

400
00:17:56,916 --> 00:17:59,083
[SKY DRAGON screeching]

401
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,625
[MAN grunts]

402
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:03,166
[screeching continues]

403
00:18:03,250 --> 00:18:06,166
Damn. Is this the end
of my handsome existence?

404
00:18:13,333 --> 00:18:15,458
Whoa, did you see that?

405
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:17,583
He completely nullified
its lightning attack.

406
00:18:17,666 --> 00:18:19,500
No way! Is he a Hero?

407
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:21,500
[SKY DRAGON screeching]

408
00:18:21,583 --> 00:18:24,500
Sheesh, compared to Charybdis,
this is easy.

409
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:26,458
♪

410
00:18:33,708 --> 00:18:34,708
Hmph.

411
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:39,541
[gasping]

412
00:18:44,875 --> 00:18:46,041
[RIMURU]
A dinner invite?

413
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,458
Yes.

414
00:18:47,541 --> 00:18:48,958
From a man named Mjolmire.

415
00:18:49,041 --> 00:18:50,750
He's a rather wealthy merchant,

416
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:53,208
and he would like you
to see the store he runs.

417
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:55,291
Apparently the children
are invited, too.

418
00:18:55,375 --> 00:18:57,541
[RIMURU]
Okay, but why me?

419
00:18:57,625 --> 00:18:59,625
[YUUKI] Oh, something about
a mysterious warrior

420
00:18:59,708 --> 00:19:01,791
saving his life today.

421
00:19:01,875 --> 00:19:05,583
He defeated a Sky Dragon.
Does that sound familiar?

422
00:19:05,666 --> 00:19:08,833
[RIMURU] Maybe it does,
maybe it doesn't.

423
00:19:08,916 --> 00:19:10,083
So this Mole guy--

424
00:19:10,166 --> 00:19:11,416
[YUUKI]
Mjolmire.

425
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,541
[RIMURU]
Whatevs, is he trustworthy?

426
00:19:13,625 --> 00:19:14,708
[YUUKI]
Well, he's earned

427
00:19:14,791 --> 00:19:15,875
the official
merchant certification

428
00:19:15,958 --> 00:19:17,166
issued by
the Kingdom of Blumund

429
00:19:17,250 --> 00:19:18,916
and the Free Union.

430
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,833
And he might have a side gig
as a loan shark

431
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:22,291
outside of the public eye.

432
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:25,166
But I ran a background check
and he is clean.

433
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,833
So I guess he's trustworthy.

434
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:28,958
[RIMURU]
Hmm.

435
00:19:29,041 --> 00:19:31,791
♪

436
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:34,875
[KIDS]
Wow!

437
00:19:34,958 --> 00:19:36,250
[KIDS chuckling]

438
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:37,708
[KIDS]
Mm!

439
00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:38,875
[GALE]
It's delicious!

440
00:19:38,958 --> 00:19:41,625
[ALICE]
It tastes like heaven!

441
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:42,750
[KIDS chatter]

442
00:19:44,250 --> 00:19:45,791
[MJOLMIRE]
So, how do you like the wine?

443
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:48,583
Nice. I approve.

444
00:19:48,666 --> 00:19:50,541
I knew that you would.

445
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:52,750
It's an excellent vintage
that I managed to procure

446
00:19:52,833 --> 00:19:55,333
just recently
via a very special route.

447
00:19:55,416 --> 00:19:56,833
Go on and pour him more.

448
00:20:01,041 --> 00:20:02,750
Uh, hey, are you sure
you don't mind

449
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,125
feeding my students, too?

450
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,000
[MJOLMIRE]
Of course not, it's my pleasure.

451
00:20:06,083 --> 00:20:08,166
I do owe you my life, after all.

452
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:10,291
Why, whatever do you mean?

453
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:13,291
Let's just say that I have
a pretty extensive network

454
00:20:13,375 --> 00:20:14,666
for gathering information,

455
00:20:14,750 --> 00:20:16,041
and even with
a different appearance

456
00:20:16,125 --> 00:20:17,833
I know very well
that you were the one

457
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,583
who saved me earlier today.

458
00:20:19,666 --> 00:20:20,833
Nothing can get past me.

459
00:20:22,875 --> 00:20:26,083
A nice dinner is a small price
to pay when I owe you my life,

460
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:28,083
and I wouldn't dream
of offending my savior.

461
00:20:28,166 --> 00:20:30,583
So, I don't know about you,

462
00:20:30,666 --> 00:20:32,416
but I think this
makes us even.

463
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,833
Wouldn't you agree, sir?

464
00:20:34,875 --> 00:20:36,291
Sure, why not?

465
00:20:36,375 --> 00:20:38,333
[RIMURU]
I guess he's pretty trustworthy

466
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:40,208
as far as merchants go.

467
00:20:40,291 --> 00:20:42,583
Quick question for you though.

468
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:44,208
Since you're so knowledgeable,

469
00:20:44,291 --> 00:20:46,750
I assume that you must know
who I am, right?

470
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,541
Correct.

471
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:49,666
[RIMURU]
Cool, cool.

472
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,666
So why don't you
come to our town?

473
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:53,875
[gasps]
Wait, are you serious?

474
00:20:53,958 --> 00:20:55,375
Your town?

475
00:20:55,458 --> 00:20:57,333
There's a lot of things
we'd like to start selling,

476
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,125
but we lack the know-how.

477
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:01,500
If we had your help,
maybe that could change.

478
00:21:01,583 --> 00:21:04,041
And then both parties
would profit.

479
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:06,375
Oh, uh, I mean,
both parties would benefit.

480
00:21:06,458 --> 00:21:08,291
[laughing]

481
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:10,125
You've got a deal.

482
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:11,666
Then it's settled.

483
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:16,791
[MJOLMIRE] Okay. With this
letter of introduction,

484
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:18,625
I should be able
to head to your town.

485
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:20,625
You should come visit again.

486
00:21:20,708 --> 00:21:23,166
I'll cut you some
extra special deals next time.

487
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,750
Yeah, I'm sure you will.

488
00:21:25,833 --> 00:21:27,791
Guard these kids.

489
00:21:27,875 --> 00:21:29,583
May the blessing
of the Queen of Spirits

490
00:21:29,666 --> 00:21:30,916
be upon you.

491
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,458
Miss, is that a magic spell?

492
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:35,625
No, it's a prayer.

493
00:21:35,708 --> 00:21:38,208
It's something we say
back in my homeland.

494
00:21:38,291 --> 00:21:39,750
It means the Queen of Spirits,

495
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:41,333
who lives in
the Dwelling of Spirits,

496
00:21:41,416 --> 00:21:42,875
will always watch over you kids.

497
00:21:42,958 --> 00:21:44,166
Hold the phone, lady!

498
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:46,666
Did you just say
the "Dwelling of Spirits?"

499
00:21:46,750 --> 00:21:48,708
Please tell me
you know where that is.

500
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:52,000
Uh, yes. I do.
I used to live there.

501
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:54,833
Well, more like in a village
near there, actually.

502
00:21:54,916 --> 00:21:56,833
[gasps in excitement]

503
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:58,791
♪

504
00:21:58,875 --> 00:22:01,083
[RIMURU]
In exchange for a generous tip,

505
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:02,583
the lady told me where to go.

506
00:22:02,666 --> 00:22:04,916
The Ulg Nature Park,

507
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,833
in the northern part
of a frontier nation

508
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:09,250
called the Republic of Ulgrasia.

509
00:22:13,125 --> 00:22:15,791
This is where
the Dwelling of Spirits is.

510
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:20,416
Shizu, I swear
that I'm gonna save these kids.

511
00:23:53,208 --> 00:23:55,708
[GREAT SAGE] Next time,
"Conquering the Labyrinth."

